#: resources/views/settings.phtml:440
msgid "Explanation of Technical Users (to define API/MCP access rights)"
msgstr ""
"Forklaring af tekniske brugere (til fastlæggelse af API-/MCP-"
"adgangsrettigheder)"

#: resources/views/settings.phtml:442
msgid ""
"By selecting a (technical) user, the access rights for API/MCP requests can "
"be specified. Any tree data requested with API/MCP is limited to the access "
"rights of the specified (technical) user."
msgstr ""
"Når der vælges en (teknisk) bruger, bestemmes adgangsrettighederne for API- "
"og MCP-forespørgsler. Data fra slægtstræer, som hentes via API/MCP, er "
"begrænset til den valgte (tekniske) brugers rettigheder."

#: resources/views/settings.phtml:443
msgid ""
"It is recommended to create a separate (technical) user, which is only used "
"to define the API/MCP access rights. The maximum access role, wich is "
"allowed for the (technical) user is limited to an \"Editor\". \"Moderators\" "
"or \"Administrators\" are denied access during API/MCP requests."
msgstr ""
"Oprettelse af en separat (teknisk) bruger anbefales. Brugeren bør "
"udelukkende anvendes til styring af API-/MCP-adgangsrettigheder. Den højeste "
"tilladte rolle er \"Redaktør\". Roller som \"Moderator\" og "
"\"Administrator\" er ikke tilladt ved API-/MCP-kald."

#: resources/views/settings.phtml:444
msgid ""
"If new records etc. are created with API/MCP, the data is created with the "
"specified (technical) user. In order to have control about the changed data, "
"it is not allowed that the selected (technical) user has \"Automatically "
"accept changes\" activated. This ensures that a moderator can always reject "
"unintended changes during a review of pending changes."
msgstr ""
"Når nye registreringer m.m. oprettes via API/MCP, registreres de under den "
"angivne (tekniske) bruger. For at sikre kontrol med ændringerne må "
"funktionen “Godkend ændringer automatisk” ikke være aktiveret for denne "
"bruger. Dermed kan en moderator altid afvise utilsigtede ændringer under "
"gennemgangen af ventende ændringer."
